summary: This is an internal FBI email chain from April 29, 2020, discussing coordination between case teams. The email requests the creation of a spreadsheet to track remaining electronic materials to be searched in an unspecified case and the Epstein case, and asks for completion estimates.
keyFacts: The email indicates the FBI's New York office was actively working on the Epstein case as of April 2020.
The email references coordination between an unspecified case team and the Epstein case team.
The email discusses the need to create a spreadsheet to track remaining electronic materials to be searched.
The email requests estimates for when the remaining investigative work will be completed.
The correspondence shows internal FBI management (an Assistant Special Agent in Charge) directing case coordination.
